WEBVTT

00:01.727 --> 00:04.578
<i> [soft music]</i>

00:04.730 --> 00:11.719
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:16.091 --> 00:18.759
- Ruby.
- Mm?

00:18.853 --> 00:21.912
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:21.930 --> 00:25.691
Hi, sweet pea.
- Mel!

00:25.768 --> 00:27.842
Oh, it really is you.

00:27.862 --> 00:30.270
- It really is me.

00:30.364 --> 00:33.348
- Why did you sneak up
on me like that, old man?

00:33.425 --> 00:36.017
- You weren't expecting me?
- No.

00:36.037 --> 00:38.037
- Oh.
- But how did you get here?

00:38.113 --> 00:39.204
- No clue.

00:39.431 --> 00:41.523
Suddenly, I was just walking
through the door.

00:41.600 --> 00:46.436
I assumed you had arranged it,
you know, island magic style.

00:46.438 --> 00:51.124
- Roarke, she knows how much
I've been missing you.

00:51.277 --> 00:56.055
She said it was impossible,
but I guess she a found way.

00:56.131 --> 00:58.131
- I'm sorry I scared you, baby.

00:58.208 --> 01:00.617
- Just come here.
Just want to feel you.

01:00.619 --> 01:02.803
Make sure you're real.

01:02.955 --> 01:10.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:10.646 --> 01:13.906
- Vanilla cream soda
as requested.

01:13.982 --> 01:15.649
I see you're enjoying
the chicken.

01:15.725 --> 01:18.985
- This seasoning
is pure Chattanooga fire.

01:19.138 --> 01:20.746
Are you sure you're
not from the South?

01:20.897 --> 01:24.991
- I have relatives from
South America, if that counts.

01:25.086 --> 01:27.086
- Mm.
- [laughs]

01:27.237 --> 01:29.663
- Jasper Dawson,
where are your manners?

01:29.815 --> 01:33.317
Where I'm from, we say
that you are a man by birth,

01:33.319 --> 01:35.743
but you're a gentleman
by choice.

01:35.763 --> 01:39.323
Thank you for having me.
- It's my absolute pleasure.

01:39.325 --> 01:42.993
So tell me, what can the island
do for you, Mr. Dawson?

01:43.011 --> 01:44.752
- Well, I'm stuck.
- You're stuck?

01:44.830 --> 01:45.846
- I'm stuck, and I don't know

01:45.998 --> 01:47.831
how to get unstuck
or get out of here.

01:47.850 --> 01:49.349
- That sounds awful.
- It is.

01:49.426 --> 01:51.777
It's like waiting
for the bus that never comes.

01:51.928 --> 01:53.428
- Okay, so talk to me
about your life

01:53.447 --> 01:56.281
before you arrived
at this awful stuck place.

01:56.433 --> 02:00.010
- Well, I'm a simple boy
from Chattanooga, Tennessee,

02:00.012 --> 02:02.955
who always loved the arts.

02:03.031 --> 02:05.457
My aspirations led me to Miami,

02:05.534 --> 02:08.610
where I opened
my very own art gallery.

02:08.629 --> 02:10.295
- Wow, that's wonderful.

02:10.372 --> 02:13.114
- Well, it was.
You know, things change.

02:13.134 --> 02:17.302
And I had a really hard time
going with the change.

02:17.379 --> 02:20.030
Ms. Roarke,
do you know what an NFT is?

02:20.032 --> 02:22.290
- Non-fungible token?

02:22.309 --> 02:25.886
- Yeah, well, try hanging one
of those on your gallery wall.

02:26.038 --> 02:27.795
- Will you excuse me
one second?

02:27.873 --> 02:28.889
I have something
to take care of.

02:29.041 --> 02:30.724
- Take your time.

02:30.800 --> 02:36.137
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:36.157 --> 02:39.733
- Oh, Elena!
Oh, my gosh, oh!

02:39.851 --> 02:42.494
Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

02:42.646 --> 02:44.721
- Mel, it's so nice
to see you again.

02:44.723 --> 02:46.314
- Thank you.

02:46.333 --> 02:49.393
Looks like you've been taking
good care of my girl.

02:49.411 --> 02:50.560
- I try.

02:50.562 --> 02:52.062
Actually, do you mind
if I steal her

02:52.064 --> 02:53.897
for a few minutes?
- Oh, of course.

02:53.899 --> 02:55.507
I'll meet you
back at the suite, okay?

02:55.584 --> 02:57.009
- Okay.

02:57.160 --> 02:58.493
- Thank you again, Ms. Roarke.

02:58.512 --> 03:00.012
- It's nothing, really.

03:00.163 --> 03:04.165
- All right.
- Bye.

03:04.167 --> 03:06.185
- Let's go talk.

03:06.261 --> 03:08.245
- You know, Elena,
I didn't even understand

03:08.263 --> 03:11.690
how much I was hurting
until I saw Mel.

03:11.841 --> 03:13.099
But you know what?

03:13.252 --> 03:15.343
You and your amazing
insight did.

03:15.362 --> 03:16.678
- Okay, Ruby.

03:16.697 --> 03:19.364
- And by the way, look,
I am so sorry I was late.

03:19.516 --> 03:20.607
- Ruby, listen.

03:20.759 --> 03:22.850
- But you know, since it was
your gift to us,

03:22.870 --> 03:24.519
I figured you'd understand.

03:24.596 --> 03:27.931
- Ruby, do you know
what today is?

03:27.950 --> 03:30.116
- Well, I mean, I could
say Monday,

03:30.269 --> 03:32.953
but I don't think that's
where you're going, is it?

03:33.071 --> 03:35.380
- Today is Día de los Muertos.

03:35.532 --> 03:36.715
- Day of the Dead?

03:36.866 --> 03:41.035
- 24 hours for those of us
still on Earth to pray

03:41.113 --> 03:43.889
and to remember our loved ones
who have died.

03:44.040 --> 03:46.391
We set up an altar,

03:46.468 --> 03:47.968
and then we fill it
with things they love

03:48.044 --> 03:50.120
so we can welcome
their spirits back.

03:50.138 --> 03:51.897
- Why you telling me this?

03:51.974 --> 03:55.976
- Because of Fantasy Island,
our loved ones,

03:56.128 --> 03:58.737
they return to us
as more than spirits.

03:58.814 --> 04:02.407
They can come in bodily form,

04:02.484 --> 04:04.910
just like they were in life.

04:05.061 --> 04:09.639
Ruby, I didn't bring Mel
to the island.

04:09.641 --> 04:12.809
- You mean Mel is...

04:12.828 --> 04:15.979
- I'm so sorry.

04:15.998 --> 04:19.741
- Mm, no, obviously
Mel is still alive.

04:19.818 --> 04:21.001
He's not dead.

04:21.153 --> 04:22.652
Mel would know if he were dead.

04:22.671 --> 04:23.745
- He might not,

04:23.764 --> 04:24.930
if it happened very recently

04:25.007 --> 04:27.432
and if he died peacefully.

04:27.584 --> 04:30.769
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:30.846 --> 04:33.330
- The kids...

04:33.423 --> 04:35.757
Elena, I can't be there
to comfort them.

04:35.834 --> 04:37.851
- I know, I know.

04:38.003 --> 04:41.171
- Mel, oh, God.

04:41.264 --> 04:44.357
[sobs]
How am I gonna tell him?

04:44.510 --> 04:48.011
[sobbing]

04:48.013 --> 04:50.938
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

04:51.033 --> 04:58.297
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:02.361 --> 05:04.027
- Thank you for waiting,
Mr. Dawson.

05:04.046 --> 05:09.290
- Ah, I swear the sun has
never felt this good before.

05:09.368 --> 05:11.551
Please, call me Jasper.

05:11.628 --> 05:14.128
- So let's start
with the basics, Jasper.

05:14.206 --> 05:15.981
How did you die?

05:16.132 --> 05:18.041
- Well, you know, doctors love

05:18.043 --> 05:20.301
to throw
their scary words around,

05:20.395 --> 05:24.381
like high cholesterol,
plaque, blockage.

05:24.399 --> 05:27.993
It's just all so unpleasant,
but maybe I should've listened.

05:28.220 --> 05:31.888
Whoops.
Now about getting me unstuck.

05:31.907 --> 05:36.226
- It sounds as if
you are in purgatory.

05:36.244 --> 05:41.823
- Wherever it is, it's lonely
and cold and boring as hell.

05:41.842 --> 05:45.235
I belong with the angels.

05:45.253 --> 05:47.512
My fantasy is to go to heaven,
Ms. Roarke.

05:47.589 --> 05:50.924
Can you help me?
- You can help yourself.

05:51.000 --> 05:52.909
You're getting
a second chance, Jasper.

05:52.928 --> 05:54.094
Not a lot of people get that.

05:54.246 --> 05:56.930
You have 24 hours
to change your fate.

05:56.932 --> 05:59.082
Now, if you fail,
you could end up stuck

05:59.101 --> 06:02.752
wherever you are forever.

06:02.754 --> 06:04.771
- You mean
in the bad place?

06:04.923 --> 06:06.848
- I mean the bad place.

06:06.867 --> 06:09.326
The good news is
it's up to you.

06:11.763 --> 06:14.373
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

06:20.881 --> 06:22.697
- Hi.
- Hey.

06:22.774 --> 06:25.792
- I'm sorry I kept you waiting.

06:25.944 --> 06:27.944
- Now, what did Ms. Roarke say?

06:27.946 --> 06:30.280
- A lot, a lot, actually.

06:30.282 --> 06:31.723
- Now, did you ask how long
I get to stay?

06:31.800 --> 06:34.375
Because I--well, I need clothes
and swim trunks,

06:34.453 --> 06:35.452
and I think I forgot--

06:35.545 --> 06:37.896
- Yeah, you're just here
for a day, Mel.

06:37.973 --> 06:40.065
- Oh, okay.
- Mm-hmm.

06:40.292 --> 06:42.884
- Then I guess we'll have
to make the most of it.

06:42.903 --> 06:45.404
Let's enjoy every minute.

06:45.597 --> 06:49.390
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:49.410 --> 06:51.076
- You know what?

06:51.153 --> 06:54.471
That's exactly
what we should do.

06:54.473 --> 06:56.081
And I know a private spot
by the beach

06:56.158 --> 06:58.808
where you won't need trunks.

06:58.902 --> 07:00.902
- Mm, lead the way.

07:00.921 --> 07:02.162
[both laugh]

07:02.238 --> 07:03.755
- Okay.
- Come on then.

07:03.907 --> 07:11.138
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:12.007 --> 07:13.581
- Morning.
- Morning.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.750
- I'm not used to
seeing you alone anymore.

07:15.769 --> 07:17.010
- Ruby's with her husband.

07:17.162 --> 07:20.421
He arrived last night
at midnight.

07:20.499 --> 07:24.609
- Oh, sorry to hear that.
I hope she's all right.

07:24.761 --> 07:25.852
Are we still on for later?

07:26.004 --> 07:27.779
- Yeah, I'll see you
at my place in an hour.

07:27.931 --> 07:30.097
- Okay.
- Morning, sir.

07:30.117 --> 07:33.118
- Ramon Abila, this
is your host, Elena Roarke.

07:33.269 --> 07:35.787
- More like my boss.
I'm here to do a job.

07:35.939 --> 07:38.123
- Mr. Abila is gonna paint
the gazebos for us.

07:38.200 --> 07:40.350
Of course, you should also
make time for yourself

07:40.368 --> 07:42.294
while you're on the island.

07:42.445 --> 07:44.370
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:44.523 --> 07:48.191
- How did you hear about me?
- It was a referral, I believe.

07:48.193 --> 07:50.210
Yes, somebody that you
used to know in Miami.

07:50.286 --> 07:53.120
So do you paint other things
or just buildings?

07:53.140 --> 07:55.248
- Nothing worth saving lately.

07:55.309 --> 07:56.958
I'm just trying
to make ends meet.

07:57.035 --> 07:58.125
- I have a meeting
this morning,

07:58.203 --> 07:59.869
but Ash is gonna get
you settled.

07:59.888 --> 08:01.204
Then you can relax for a bit.

08:01.297 --> 08:03.464
We don't have to start
the job until later.

08:03.484 --> 08:04.966
- Works for me.

08:05.043 --> 08:06.651
- Welcome to Fantasy Island.

08:06.728 --> 08:10.563
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:10.716 --> 08:13.566
<i> [mellow music]</i>

08:13.643 --> 08:19.247
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:20.834 --> 08:23.043
- Jasper?

08:24.746 --> 08:26.338
- Ramon?

08:26.414 --> 08:27.747
- You're supposed to be dead.

08:27.899 --> 08:31.918
- Well, I am, usually.

08:31.995 --> 08:33.920
It's complicated,

08:33.997 --> 08:36.422
but I'm so tickled
to see you, Ramon.

08:36.575 --> 08:37.907
- Is that right?

08:37.926 --> 08:40.001
'Cause I'm gonna kick your ass.

08:40.078 --> 08:41.594
- [exclaims softly]

08:41.747 --> 08:43.688
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:43.765 --> 08:45.982
[grunting]

08:49.363 --> 08:51.029
- Ramon, you're obviously
in a bit of a tizz.

08:51.222 --> 08:52.756
- I saw the spreadsheets
on your computer.

08:52.774 --> 08:54.181
You cheated me!

08:54.259 --> 08:56.368
- That was a misunderstanding.
I can explain.

08:56.444 --> 08:58.094
- I should have known
that the guy who thought

08:58.113 --> 09:00.187
selling forged paintings
was a good idea

09:00.207 --> 09:02.690
was gonna turn around
and stab me in the back!

09:02.768 --> 09:05.544
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:05.620 --> 09:06.936
- I paid you!

09:06.955 --> 09:09.439
- You made me think
that you cared about me,

09:09.457 --> 09:11.124
that you were helping me,
and then you turn around

09:11.276 --> 09:13.109
and lied about what you were
getting for my paintings!

09:13.128 --> 09:15.387
- Your forgeries,
if you want to be technical.

09:15.538 --> 09:17.964
And you went through my files!
Those are private.

09:18.041 --> 09:20.725
- I thought you were dead.
- I am dead.

09:20.877 --> 09:23.469
- You will be
once I get my hands on you.

09:23.622 --> 09:25.288
- You're a liar.

09:25.381 --> 09:26.547
- Oh! Oh.

09:26.567 --> 09:29.626
- Where are you going?

09:29.628 --> 09:31.403
Come back here, liar!

09:31.479 --> 09:33.738
- [whimpering]

09:33.890 --> 09:36.575
Hello. Oh!

09:36.726 --> 09:39.393
- Running away?

09:39.471 --> 09:41.580
- I have to go.

09:41.731 --> 09:44.583
We'll talk later, Ramon.
Toodles!

09:44.734 --> 09:47.143
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:47.145 --> 09:48.753
- What is Jasper doing here?

09:48.830 --> 09:50.589
He's supposed to be dead.

09:50.740 --> 09:52.239
- Oh, he's dead.

09:52.317 --> 09:54.317
On Fantasy Island,
spirits can return

09:54.410 --> 09:56.986
in human form
on Día De Los Muertos.

09:57.005 --> 09:59.931
- That's crazy.
- Well...

10:00.008 --> 10:01.415
- You called me for him

10:01.435 --> 10:02.842
because you want me
to forgive him or something?

10:02.994 --> 10:04.327
'Cause that's not happening.

10:04.329 --> 10:06.938
- You're here for Jasper
and also for you, Ramon.

10:07.165 --> 10:09.524
Nobody ends up
on Fantasy Island by accident.

10:10.927 --> 10:12.685
I'm hearing a little pain
in your voice.

10:12.762 --> 10:15.030
- Not pain.

10:16.358 --> 10:18.283
Anger.

10:18.434 --> 10:22.746
- How did you meet Jasper?

10:26.534 --> 10:30.353
- My childhood was rough.
Dad died.

10:30.446 --> 10:31.963
My mom had to work three jobs.

10:32.115 --> 10:34.207
To cope, when I was about 12,

10:34.283 --> 10:36.042
I started doing a lot
of graffiti art.

10:36.194 --> 10:38.862
One night, I was bombing
the side of a building,

10:38.864 --> 10:41.622
and Jasper ran out yelling.

10:41.642 --> 10:44.050
Turns out he was an art dealer,

10:44.202 --> 10:46.719
and it was his gallery
that I was bombing.

10:46.872 --> 10:48.462
- And he liked your work.

10:48.540 --> 10:49.931
<i> [soft music]</i>

10:49.983 --> 10:53.318
- He looked out for me.

10:53.395 --> 10:57.656
He cared almost like a father.

10:57.732 --> 11:02.494
After he died,
I found out it was all a lie.

11:02.645 --> 11:04.220
He betrayed me.

11:04.239 --> 11:07.056
- Maybe that's why
you're both here,

11:07.075 --> 11:10.669
so you can tell him
how you feel.

11:10.820 --> 11:14.764
- You know what?
I'll pass.

11:14.766 --> 11:21.763
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:24.000 --> 11:26.926
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

11:27.078 --> 11:33.525
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:34.361 --> 11:36.510
- I let myself in.
Hope you don't mind.

11:36.530 --> 11:38.087
- Not at all.

11:38.106 --> 11:39.847
- Got the stuff
you told me to bring.

11:39.866 --> 11:41.408
Dani's favorites.

11:43.778 --> 11:47.021
Beer, salami with Swiss.

11:47.098 --> 11:48.540
I may have eaten
the other half.

11:48.691 --> 11:50.458
- [chuckles]

11:51.953 --> 11:53.336
- That time in Afghanistan.

11:55.198 --> 11:57.716
- The calaca
to represent Dani.

11:57.792 --> 11:59.592
It's perfect.

12:02.130 --> 12:03.613
- Look, thanks for doing this.

12:03.673 --> 12:04.556
There's some things
I need to say, and--

12:04.707 --> 12:07.308
- You don't have
to explain, Javier.

12:07.969 --> 12:09.043
- So what do I do?

12:09.062 --> 12:10.395
- Well, the calaca
and the objects

12:10.546 --> 12:13.047
that you brought it
to represent the four elements,

12:13.124 --> 12:16.459
earth, air, spirit, and fire,
that's what's important.

12:16.478 --> 12:20.321
Now it can help
if you say a few words.

12:26.062 --> 12:28.580
- Hey, buddy.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.583
Look, I'm sure
you're pissed at me.

12:31.659 --> 12:33.334
That's on me.

12:35.981 --> 12:38.314
You're my best friend.

12:38.333 --> 12:41.909
I hope that counts
for something.

12:41.928 --> 12:44.912
<i> [gentle music]</i>

12:44.931 --> 12:46.914
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:46.933 --> 12:48.099
How was that?

12:48.176 --> 12:50.843
- Just right.
Now you wait.

12:50.996 --> 12:54.347
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:54.499 --> 12:56.182
- How about you?

12:56.334 --> 12:58.184
Is there anybody
you bring back on this day?

12:58.261 --> 13:00.278
- I honor my ancestors
every day.

13:00.429 --> 13:02.030
- That's not what I asked.

13:03.266 --> 13:05.950
- Well, there's someone
that I...

13:06.027 --> 13:07.844
that I think about
bringing back,

13:07.862 --> 13:09.770
my cousin Fernando.

13:09.790 --> 13:11.122
There are so many things to say

13:11.274 --> 13:13.541
I wouldn't even know
where to begin.

13:14.686 --> 13:15.960
- You might as well try.

13:16.112 --> 13:18.021
That's what I finally decided.

13:18.023 --> 13:20.256
Can't just carry it with me.

13:21.284 --> 13:23.134
The burden's too heavy,
you know?

13:32.887 --> 13:34.312
- Now, is it just me,

13:34.389 --> 13:37.557
or was this tattoo
a lot less when you got it?

13:37.633 --> 13:39.633
- Oh, yeah, it grew.

13:39.653 --> 13:42.970
As soon you left,
it just kind of expanded.

13:43.048 --> 13:46.307
Don't ask me why,
'cause I don't know.

13:46.384 --> 13:48.568
Other than that, it's a sign
that I'm supposed to be here.

13:48.720 --> 13:50.553
- Hmm. I like it.

13:50.555 --> 13:53.289
- Hmm. Me too.

13:57.320 --> 13:58.986
- Something you want
to tell me?

13:59.064 --> 14:00.654
- No, nothing, nothing.

14:00.674 --> 14:03.424
Honey, I'm just happy
to be here with you.

14:04.752 --> 14:06.694
- Permission to float a theory?

14:06.696 --> 14:08.237
- Permission granted.

14:08.256 --> 14:12.333
- I think you met someone,
but you're afraid to tell me

14:12.410 --> 14:14.243
because you don't want
to hurt me.

14:14.262 --> 14:18.431
- Well, three for imagination,
and zero for accuracy.

14:18.583 --> 14:21.250
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:21.252 --> 14:23.086
- Was my coming here a mistake?

14:23.104 --> 14:25.104
- No!
Mel, this is the best thing

14:25.181 --> 14:27.056
that's happened
since I've been here.

14:27.058 --> 14:29.683
- Permission to float a theory?
- Denied.

14:29.761 --> 14:32.019
- Well, then I'll just say
whatever it is,

14:32.038 --> 14:36.374
or whoever it is, it's okay.

14:36.601 --> 14:38.543
- Mel, you're dead.

14:38.620 --> 14:40.453
You died.

14:40.529 --> 14:42.547
I'm so sorry.

14:42.698 --> 14:44.273
- Well, you're talking crazy.

14:44.292 --> 14:45.291
- No, the reason
why you're here

14:45.443 --> 14:48.628
is because today
is Día de Los Muertos.

14:48.704 --> 14:51.464
- But a dead man
can't feel the sun on his face

14:51.540 --> 14:52.557
or smell the ocean.

14:52.708 --> 14:55.042
- I know, but here you can.

14:55.120 --> 14:58.229
And just for today.

14:58.381 --> 15:00.064
Honey, I called you here,

15:00.216 --> 15:01.715
and I didn't even know
I was doing it.

15:01.809 --> 15:04.310
- No, Ruby, I am not dead!

15:04.462 --> 15:06.312
- Honey, I should have
told you sooner,

15:06.464 --> 15:07.888
but I didn't know at first.

15:08.024 --> 15:10.742
- No, no, I don't want to hear
any more of this foolishness.

15:11.560 --> 15:14.370
You know, maybe me coming here
really was a mistake.

15:15.657 --> 15:17.415
- Mel!

15:17.566 --> 15:24.339
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:24.907 --> 15:27.074
- Oh, come on!

15:27.093 --> 15:28.593
<i> [light playful music]</i>

15:28.595 --> 15:29.819
Let's go!

15:29.837 --> 15:31.821
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:31.839 --> 15:34.432
Go, go, go!

15:34.509 --> 15:36.159
Ahh! Oh, uh...

15:36.161 --> 15:39.437
- This is not the highway
to heaven.

15:39.588 --> 15:40.980
Come with me, please.

15:45.019 --> 15:46.169
- I'd love
to dig a little deeper

15:46.187 --> 15:48.446
into this
"get Jasper into heaven" plan

15:48.523 --> 15:51.841
because I feel that hellfire
is licking at my heels.

15:51.859 --> 15:53.176
- Oh, the plan is simple.

15:53.194 --> 15:56.955
You figure out why you're stuck
so you can fix it.

15:57.031 --> 16:01.033
- Cool, yeah,
but what about Ramon?

16:01.186 --> 16:03.019
He didn't seem
that thrilled to see me.

16:03.021 --> 16:05.688
- Okay, let's talk inside.
- Okay.

16:05.690 --> 16:08.949
- So what do you think?

16:08.969 --> 16:10.860
- Oh, no.
- What?

16:10.862 --> 16:12.878
- No, no, no, no.

16:12.973 --> 16:18.718
No, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no!

16:18.812 --> 16:21.554
Oh, dang it all!

16:21.706 --> 16:22.814
- What's wrong, Jasper?

16:22.890 --> 16:25.799
Isn't this your gallery,
your--your baby?

16:25.819 --> 16:27.819
- This is my purgatory!

16:27.970 --> 16:29.895
I was stuck in here
since I died,

16:30.048 --> 16:33.825
in some timeless void
staring at blank walls.

16:33.901 --> 16:35.384
- This is a lovely space.

16:35.403 --> 16:37.328
I mean, I agree with you,
it's a little bare, but--

16:37.555 --> 16:38.329
- Oh!

16:38.406 --> 16:41.240
- There, that's much better.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.484
Shall we take a spin
around the room?

16:43.503 --> 16:44.961
- Yeah.

16:46.655 --> 16:51.250
I can't stand this newfangled,
self-indulgent so-called art.

16:51.327 --> 16:53.919
I mean, what do you feel
when you see this?

16:54.072 --> 16:58.349
- I feel bad for your roommate
Maxwell Reid.

16:58.426 --> 17:02.854
You know, that's the key
to your first apartment, 1988.

17:02.930 --> 17:04.188
And then you ran out,

17:04.265 --> 17:06.357
and Maxwell had to pay
all of your back rent.

17:06.434 --> 17:09.935
- Well, I was saving money
to rent a gallery space.

17:10.088 --> 17:13.272
Put every penny I made
towards that.

17:13.349 --> 17:16.701
- Oh, sweet ride, Jasper.

17:16.778 --> 17:18.761
- Her name was Sally.

17:18.763 --> 17:20.429
- Oh, my, Jasper.

17:20.431 --> 17:23.266
You totaled Sally, and then
you gave her a cheap paint job

17:23.284 --> 17:26.193
and sold her
to an unsuspecting neighbor.

17:26.212 --> 17:28.028
- Who was cheating on his wife

17:28.122 --> 17:30.364
with the bag girl
at the Piggly Wiggly.

17:30.383 --> 17:32.383
I don't feel bad
about that one.

17:32.460 --> 17:34.126
No, sir, I do not.

17:34.279 --> 17:36.262
You know what? Let's move on.

17:37.832 --> 17:41.208
Doesn't look familiar,
so shall we?

17:41.286 --> 17:45.121
- That is the first painting
that Ramon forged for you.

17:45.123 --> 17:46.880
A heads up before you speak.

17:46.900 --> 17:48.140
The road to hell

17:48.293 --> 17:50.126
is not actually paved
with good intentions.

17:50.144 --> 17:52.478
In reality,
it's paved with lies.

17:52.572 --> 17:54.721
- Fine, it's Ramon's.

17:54.799 --> 17:57.817
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:57.893 --> 17:59.560
He's so talented.

17:59.637 --> 18:01.637
Even as a kid,
I could see that in him.

18:01.656 --> 18:03.730
- And teaching a young man
to use his talent

18:03.808 --> 18:04.990
to cheat others,

18:05.085 --> 18:07.159
that's an interesting way
to mentor, you know?

18:07.253 --> 18:08.811
- We were just gonna
do it once,

18:08.830 --> 18:10.813
and then it went so well.

18:10.906 --> 18:12.590
I knew that I could sell more
and more and more.

18:12.741 --> 18:15.484
And it's not like
I didn't give Ramon a cut.

18:15.486 --> 18:16.743
- But you told him
you sold them

18:16.763 --> 18:19.580
for less than half
of the actual price, Jasper.

18:19.657 --> 18:21.006
- I needed the money.

18:21.159 --> 18:23.434
Galleries are a money pit,
Ms. Roarke.

18:23.586 --> 18:24.844
- And what about Ramon?

18:24.996 --> 18:26.587
- He was making money
as an artist.

18:26.606 --> 18:30.608
Yes, forgeries, but that's
better than most artists do.

18:30.759 --> 18:32.926
- Jasper, Ramon trusted you.

18:33.004 --> 18:36.505
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:36.599 --> 18:38.174
- Why can't I move?

18:38.267 --> 18:40.860
- You spent a lifetime cutting
corners, shading the truth,

18:41.012 --> 18:42.269
using people
to get what you wanted,

18:42.347 --> 18:44.771
and you see, the island
didn't bring back Maxwell

18:44.791 --> 18:45.939
or your cheating neighbor.

18:45.959 --> 18:47.683
The island brought back Ramon.

18:47.702 --> 18:50.962
- Who hates my guts
worse than anyone.

18:51.113 --> 18:53.356
So how is that fair?

18:53.358 --> 18:58.527
Oh, no,
I'm in H-E-double hockey--ahh!

18:58.546 --> 18:59.745
[grunts]

18:59.822 --> 19:02.181
Oh...

19:05.052 --> 19:07.979
Okay, Ramon,
take your best shot.

19:15.229 --> 19:17.971
Oh, come on, Ramon.
You're not a house painter.

19:18.049 --> 19:19.640
You are an artist.

19:19.717 --> 19:23.402
I'm sorry I lied to you,
but I've seen the light.

19:23.479 --> 19:26.555
And I wasn't all bad.
I taught you art history.

19:26.574 --> 19:28.908
I taught you how
to tie a bow tie.

19:29.060 --> 19:31.243
- I looked up to you.

19:31.320 --> 19:33.337
You could have
nurtured my talent.

19:33.489 --> 19:34.988
Instead, you took advantage
of it, and then you died,

19:35.066 --> 19:37.233
and you left me with nothing.

19:37.251 --> 19:39.177
That's why I'm a house painter.

19:39.253 --> 19:41.846
- So now I can apologize,
and we can move on.

19:41.997 --> 19:43.181
- Why would I do that?

19:43.332 --> 19:46.017
- Because you're a good kid
with a good heart.

19:46.093 --> 19:48.761
And, Ramon,
I will be in purgatory

19:48.879 --> 19:52.097
for the rest of time,
or even worse, the bad place.

19:52.174 --> 19:53.749
- I get it.

19:53.751 --> 19:55.342
Just like you held my future
in your hands for so long,

19:55.361 --> 19:58.345
now I hold
your eternal future in mine.

19:58.364 --> 20:00.990
- Yeah, that about sums it up.

20:01.868 --> 20:04.427
- It looks like you're screwed.

20:04.445 --> 20:06.853
- Oh, Ramon.

20:06.931 --> 20:13.953
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:14.047 --> 20:15.546
- The flowers you asked for.

20:15.698 --> 20:17.273
- Beautiful, Segundo.

20:17.275 --> 20:18.549
- But I don't like this.

20:18.701 --> 20:19.942
- I need to help him.

20:19.961 --> 20:22.294
[speaking Spanish]

20:22.447 --> 20:25.130
- Fernando's spirit
is too troubled.

20:25.283 --> 20:26.724
- Well, I think maybe it's time

20:26.875 --> 20:28.059
to lay down the burden,
Segundo.

20:28.135 --> 20:32.788
- Well, that I agree with.
- Elena, I'm sorry.

20:32.807 --> 20:34.214
- Yeah?
- Have you seen Mel?

20:34.234 --> 20:36.883
I told him that he was dead.
Now I can't find him.

20:36.903 --> 20:39.645
What happens
if I can't find him?

20:39.797 --> 20:42.406
What?
What did that look mean?

20:42.483 --> 20:45.301
- With people that refuse
to accept that they have died,

20:45.303 --> 20:48.562
sometimes they get--
they get very angry.

20:48.581 --> 20:50.063
- And lost.

20:50.083 --> 20:54.085
- Okay, then what happens
after angry and lost?

20:54.161 --> 20:56.495
- Just give him a little time.
He'll come around.

20:56.647 --> 20:58.238
- Elena, I'm so scared.

20:58.316 --> 21:01.908
- Don't worry, okay?
Don't.

21:01.986 --> 21:04.820
<i> [tense music]</i>

21:04.822 --> 21:07.006
- She's crazy.

21:07.158 --> 21:10.434
I can't be dead.
It doesn't make any damn sense.

21:10.661 --> 21:13.920
- Yoo-hoo!

21:13.940 --> 21:16.682
I'm talking to you!

21:16.834 --> 21:19.259
Can you hear me?

21:19.353 --> 21:22.688
I'm talking to you!

21:22.765 --> 21:25.007
Hello?

21:25.009 --> 21:26.951
Oh, my goodness!
- Hey!

21:27.028 --> 21:30.012
- Where'd you come from?
- That's a long story.

21:30.031 --> 21:33.291
I was home, and now I'm here,

21:33.367 --> 21:37.853
and, well, you know, it all
kind of goes a little blank

21:37.872 --> 21:40.131
in the middle of there,
I'm sorry.

21:40.282 --> 21:42.358
- Well, never mind.
I'm Jasper.

21:42.376 --> 21:45.210
- Oh, Mel.
I'm in a fight with my wife.

21:45.287 --> 21:47.046
- Well, I'm in a fight
with God.

21:47.198 --> 21:48.789
But she's giving me
the silent treatment.

21:48.808 --> 21:49.974
- Is that right?

21:50.125 --> 21:51.976
- So tell me, Mel,
what do you do

21:52.053 --> 21:53.886
when you're at odds
with the Mrs.?

21:53.962 --> 21:57.706
- Oh, I hit some golf balls,
cool off.

21:57.708 --> 22:01.560
And there are my clubs,
because of course.

22:01.712 --> 22:04.655
- Well, there you go.
Don't mind if I do.

22:04.732 --> 22:07.474
<i> [soft music]</i>

22:07.493 --> 22:10.386
Oops.

22:10.388 --> 22:13.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:23.584 --> 22:26.569
<i> [soft music]</i>

22:26.587 --> 22:30.589
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:30.666 --> 22:32.424
- [laughs]

22:32.577 --> 22:35.077
Well, if you had to bring me
back from the dead,

22:35.096 --> 22:37.596
well done on the view.

22:37.748 --> 22:41.250
- So damn good to see you.
- Wait, I need to know.

22:41.343 --> 22:43.176
This gonna get all mushy
and stuff?

22:43.254 --> 22:46.088
- Yeah, it's possible.
- Mm-hmm.

22:46.181 --> 22:48.107
Well, then we're
gonna need beer.

22:48.201 --> 22:49.200
- Dani--

22:49.351 --> 22:53.520
- Mm, beer first,
mushy talk later.

22:53.598 --> 22:55.021
- Okay.

22:55.041 --> 22:58.267
- Good to see you, you big sap.

22:58.269 --> 23:00.544
[chuckles]
- Thanks for coming.

23:02.440 --> 23:03.297
[laughs]

23:07.035 --> 23:08.611
- Plays all sorts
of sports, right?

23:08.704 --> 23:10.963
[both laughing]

23:11.115 --> 23:13.799
- Oh, no!
- Mm-hmm.

23:13.951 --> 23:16.285
- Oh, she cut off
all her gorgeous hair.

23:16.287 --> 23:18.896
- She said it bugged her
on the volleyball court, so...

23:18.973 --> 23:22.808
- Oh, she looks happy.

23:22.960 --> 23:25.236
She misses you, but she is.

23:25.387 --> 23:31.409
And look who is obsessed
with fishing.

23:31.560 --> 23:34.769
- Oh, that's my girl.

23:34.771 --> 23:37.898
<i> [soft music]</i>

23:37.975 --> 23:39.642
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:39.660 --> 23:43.254
And the new wife?

23:43.330 --> 23:45.071
Come on.

23:45.149 --> 23:47.149
It's been six years
since I died.

23:47.151 --> 23:49.334
Mike better have a new wife.

23:49.487 --> 23:52.821
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:52.823 --> 23:55.933
- Debra, she's a teacher,

23:56.084 --> 23:57.768
apparently really
into bird watching.

23:57.845 --> 24:00.587
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:00.665 --> 24:02.231
You okay?

24:04.610 --> 24:06.760
- Do they laugh a lot?

24:06.779 --> 24:08.446
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah?

24:08.597 --> 24:11.640
And the kids like her?

24:11.676 --> 24:14.618
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay.

24:14.695 --> 24:17.513
Good for him.

24:17.515 --> 24:19.165
Mm.

24:21.702 --> 24:23.368
Now it's your turn.

24:23.445 --> 24:26.613
- To marry your husband?
I told you he's taken.

24:26.632 --> 24:30.784
- No, move on from the past,
find peace.

24:30.861 --> 24:33.712
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:33.789 --> 24:35.121
- That's why I asked you
to come.

24:35.141 --> 24:38.809
Dani, if--
- Don't ask me to forgive you.

24:38.961 --> 24:41.795
I won't do it.

24:41.797 --> 24:45.057
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:45.133 --> 24:48.819
You have nothing
to be forgiven for, Javi.

24:48.896 --> 24:51.805
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:51.824 --> 24:53.549
Don't you get it?

24:53.551 --> 24:57.569
The only person here
not at peace is you.

24:57.722 --> 24:59.054
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:59.073 --> 25:00.981
<i> - ♪ Please, as you are ♪</i>

25:01.000 --> 25:05.410
<i> ♪ That's good enough by far ♪</i>

25:05.487 --> 25:09.489
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:09.509 --> 25:12.417
<i> [tense music]</i>

25:12.570 --> 25:15.571
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:15.589 --> 25:18.516
- Fernando.

25:18.667 --> 25:21.760
Please, cousin.

25:21.912 --> 25:23.020
I want to talk.

25:23.171 --> 25:25.005
Let me help you, Fernando.

25:25.082 --> 25:27.340
Come on, Fernando, come on.

25:27.360 --> 25:30.510
Come on.

25:30.588 --> 25:33.756
- I don't set out
to do wrong, Mel.

25:33.774 --> 25:36.108
Wrong just seems to find me.

25:36.184 --> 25:39.703
I think it's because
I'm so dang charming.

25:39.930 --> 25:41.354
People just want
to give me things,

25:41.432 --> 25:43.023
and I took advantage of that.

25:43.100 --> 25:44.933
- Well, that's no excuse
for being an ass.

25:44.952 --> 25:46.952
- I guess
it doesn't matter now.

25:47.029 --> 25:49.772
I've lost Ramon forever.

25:49.774 --> 25:51.456
He hates me.

25:51.609 --> 25:53.942
I'm gonna go to hell
in a hand basket

25:54.003 --> 25:56.053
without the hand basket.

25:56.130 --> 25:58.088
- Do you know that your eyes

25:58.240 --> 26:00.874
well up a little bit
every time you say his name?

26:00.893 --> 26:02.393
- Allergies.

26:02.469 --> 26:04.970
- Oh, same thing happens to me
when I talk about my son,

26:05.047 --> 26:07.289
especially when things
aren't right between us.

26:07.308 --> 26:09.141
- You know it's all
a big crutch, Mel.

26:09.217 --> 26:12.052
The smile,
the delightful turn of phrase--

26:12.071 --> 26:14.146
just tools
to hide the little boy

26:14.222 --> 26:16.056
who was ignored
on the playground.

26:16.133 --> 26:18.224
- Maybe it's time
that little boy grows up.

26:18.302 --> 26:20.894
- I always wanted
to evolve into a better man.

26:20.913 --> 26:22.971
I really did,
but time slips away.

26:22.990 --> 26:26.125
Now, it's too late.
Dead is dead.

26:27.494 --> 26:30.646
- Well, things work a little
differently around here.

26:30.664 --> 26:32.906
Here's what I know.

26:32.925 --> 26:35.834
The island wouldn't
set you up to fail.

26:35.911 --> 26:37.911
Don't give up on Ramon.

26:37.930 --> 26:40.155
- Do you think
he really might forgive me?

26:40.157 --> 26:44.343
- Well, I think fathers
mess up a lot.

26:44.495 --> 26:46.178
"I'm sorry" goes a long way.

26:46.330 --> 26:50.349
- You made it sound simple
admitting that you did wrong.

26:50.501 --> 26:54.945
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:55.097 --> 26:56.280
- Do you know when I get

26:56.282 --> 26:58.357
the absolute maddest
at my wife?

26:58.433 --> 26:59.858
- Tell me.

27:00.010 --> 27:03.436
- It's when I know
that she's right,

27:03.456 --> 27:06.957
like I'm starting to think
that she is right now.

27:08.794 --> 27:13.705
Well, I've got some apologizing
to do right now, in fact.

27:13.782 --> 27:16.041
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:16.193 --> 27:18.952
I hope to see you
on the other side, Jasper.

27:19.029 --> 27:21.788
- Well, I wouldn't count on it.
- [chuckles]

27:21.807 --> 27:26.644
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:26.795 --> 27:30.555
Hey.
- Hey.

27:30.632 --> 27:31.798
- I'm sorry.

27:31.817 --> 27:33.651
- Oh, forgive him!

27:33.727 --> 27:36.970
He's sweet, and he is so wise.

27:36.989 --> 27:39.564
- And I didn't mean to scare
you running off like that.

27:39.641 --> 27:41.158
- I'm sorry too.

27:41.309 --> 27:42.901
I should have found
a better way to tell you.

27:42.903 --> 27:46.405
- Well, I don't think there's
a lot of good ways to say it.

27:46.481 --> 27:53.379
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:05.259 --> 28:08.744
- Oh, you're here.
Thank God.

28:08.762 --> 28:10.262
- I was hoping you'd come.

28:10.414 --> 28:12.080
Do you know
what you have to do?

28:12.082 --> 28:15.317
- I do, but Ms. Roarke,
I need your help.

28:20.700 --> 28:22.424
- What is this?

28:22.426 --> 28:24.259
- Jasper's final exhibition

28:24.261 --> 28:28.205
featuring a very talented
young artist.

28:28.282 --> 28:31.024
You have a gift.
- I don't understand.

28:31.026 --> 28:34.603
This is everything I've done
since I was a kid,

28:34.621 --> 28:36.029
but I threw it all out.

28:36.106 --> 28:39.107
I never thought
it was good enough.

28:39.126 --> 28:42.886
- And I pulled every last piece
out of the trash.

28:42.963 --> 28:44.780
- I'll leave you two to talk.

28:44.782 --> 28:48.208
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:48.227 --> 28:49.375
- Why?

28:49.395 --> 28:54.047
- Because I believe in you.
I always did.

28:54.066 --> 28:58.026
And I knew that someday
you would want these.

28:59.797 --> 29:02.965
I love you like a son.

29:02.983 --> 29:07.636
You trusted me,
and I messed up.

29:07.638 --> 29:09.062
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:09.081 --> 29:12.082
No excuses, just a message.

29:12.159 --> 29:14.643
You have a gift.

29:14.645 --> 29:17.087
Do not waste it.

29:17.239 --> 29:18.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:18.573 --> 29:21.650
If you'll excuse me,
I have a date with destiny.

29:21.652 --> 29:28.557
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:29.693 --> 29:31.918
- I'm really dead.

29:32.012 --> 29:34.513
- You really are.
- How?

29:34.589 --> 29:38.258
- I don't know, but Elena says
she thinks it was peaceful.

29:38.335 --> 29:40.168
- You know,
it's gonna be hard on the kids

29:40.170 --> 29:43.947
losing both of us
the same year.

29:44.024 --> 29:45.949
- You're such a good man, Mel,

29:46.026 --> 29:48.026
always thinking
of other people.

29:48.103 --> 29:50.621
- Oh, I'm scared, Ruby.

29:50.697 --> 29:53.624
What's gonna happen to me
at midnight, you know?

29:53.700 --> 29:54.866
Where will I go?

29:55.019 --> 29:56.868
- Honey, I don't know.

29:56.945 --> 29:59.630
Wherever it is, I should have
been there waiting for you.

29:59.781 --> 30:04.209
- No, you're exactly where
you're supposed to be.

30:04.361 --> 30:07.529
Can I make a confession?

30:07.548 --> 30:10.032
I miss us being us.

30:10.050 --> 30:11.809
I like those old people
with the creaky knees.

30:12.036 --> 30:14.311
[both laugh]

30:14.462 --> 30:17.539
It's crazy, huh?
- Crazy beautiful.

30:17.558 --> 30:18.816
- Yeah.

30:18.892 --> 30:21.043
- You know, we've got
a lot to be proud of.

30:21.061 --> 30:23.636
- Mm.
- Best kids in the world.

30:23.656 --> 30:25.989
- Yeah, cutest grandkids.

30:26.099 --> 30:28.233
You know, that's 'cause
they all look just like me.

30:28.385 --> 30:30.476
- What?

30:30.554 --> 30:32.645
You...

30:32.723 --> 30:36.408
[both laughing]

30:36.560 --> 30:39.244
<i> [uplifting music]</i>

30:39.321 --> 30:40.245
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:40.397 --> 30:45.158
- Damn, we're old.
- As the hills.

30:45.235 --> 30:48.661
But I had a good life.
I mean, a really good life.

30:48.663 --> 30:49.847
- The best.

30:50.074 --> 30:52.332
I bet your funeral
was standing room only.

30:52.409 --> 30:53.425
- Well, yours was.

30:53.519 --> 30:55.594
I told the kids
that I scattered your ashes

30:55.746 --> 30:58.747
during the trip, but we had
one hell of a homegoing.

30:58.807 --> 31:01.449
- I bet you did!

31:01.451 --> 31:03.602
- So many memories, you and me.

31:03.696 --> 31:05.178
You remember when MJ smashed

31:05.197 --> 31:09.015
Ellie's birthday cake
in her face?

31:09.093 --> 31:11.109
- We thought she'd be so mad,

31:11.186 --> 31:14.687
but she licked it off,
just as calm as can be.

31:14.765 --> 31:17.933
- Yeah, she took after you,
that's why.

31:17.951 --> 31:22.170
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:26.276 --> 31:28.886
- Thanks for the slideshow
and for keeping up

31:28.962 --> 31:31.296
with my crazy family
after all these years.

31:31.373 --> 31:34.299
- Hey, Dani...
- Oh, I already told you.

31:34.376 --> 31:37.895
- No, listen,
I need to say this, okay?

31:38.046 --> 31:41.047
I'm sorry that you died
and I didn't.

31:41.066 --> 31:44.793
- I'm sorry I died too.

31:44.811 --> 31:47.646
But I'm not sorry you didn't.

31:47.722 --> 31:50.407
Look, if you want
to do something for me,

31:50.558 --> 31:52.317
Javi, do this.

31:52.469 --> 31:56.246
Live, fall in love,
make mistakes.

31:56.473 --> 31:59.249
If you want to tell stories
about me at my kids' wedding,

31:59.326 --> 32:03.828
that would be great,
but this is your life.

32:03.981 --> 32:07.332
Live it like crazy for me.

32:07.409 --> 32:10.652
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:10.671 --> 32:13.838
See you on the other side.

32:13.915 --> 32:15.415
- See you.

32:15.434 --> 32:22.314
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:37.957 --> 32:39.748
- I'm never gonna
wear a bow tie.

32:42.294 --> 32:46.688
- But at least you'll know
how to tie one.

32:46.690 --> 32:48.632
You came.

32:48.709 --> 32:55.714
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:55.866 --> 32:59.476
- What time is it?
- It's 11:58.

32:59.627 --> 33:01.311
But no one's counting.

33:01.388 --> 33:03.963
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:03.983 --> 33:06.208
- It wasn't just
about the money.

33:06.210 --> 33:08.226
I mean, it was definitely
about the money,

33:08.303 --> 33:11.488
but I was also mad at you
for dying.

33:11.565 --> 33:16.051
- Well, I was mad at me, too,
for dying and the money.

33:16.069 --> 33:19.237
- You were like a father
to me, Jasper.

33:19.389 --> 33:22.907
Not father of the year maybe,
but it still counts.

33:23.060 --> 33:25.168
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:25.320 --> 33:30.749
- Does this mean
that you forgive me?

33:30.901 --> 33:32.509
- I forgive you.

33:32.586 --> 33:34.753
- Thank you.

33:34.829 --> 33:42.019
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:42.855 --> 33:45.188
Will you stay with me?

33:46.266 --> 33:48.750
- I'm not going anywhere.

33:48.752 --> 33:55.991
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:58.095 --> 33:59.852
- You know what this means?

33:59.930 --> 34:02.447
- What?
- It's official now.

34:02.524 --> 34:03.707
Since I'm dead,

34:03.858 --> 34:05.784
we are no longer married,

34:05.860 --> 34:07.285
and you have no excuse

34:07.362 --> 34:09.120
not to go forward
and live your life.

34:09.197 --> 34:12.031
- That's a little bit scary.

34:12.051 --> 34:16.444
- It's time to shed the cocoon
and turn into a butterfly.

34:16.463 --> 34:18.630
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:18.782 --> 34:21.224
So what's her name?
- Who?

34:21.301 --> 34:24.619
- The woman you so obviously
aren't telling me about.

34:24.638 --> 34:26.788
- Gina.

34:26.790 --> 34:28.565
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:28.716 --> 34:32.736
- When I come back next year,
introduce me.

34:34.798 --> 34:36.907
Longer than a lifetime.

34:36.983 --> 34:40.410
- And more than all the world.

34:40.562 --> 34:43.729
I love you, Mel.

34:43.731 --> 34:50.295
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:52.666 --> 34:54.174
- Are you afraid?

34:55.427 --> 34:56.593
- Not anymore.

34:56.744 --> 35:03.725
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:30.871 --> 35:33.296
- Fernando!

35:33.448 --> 35:35.298
Let me help you, Fernando!

35:38.879 --> 35:41.863
<i> [tense music]</i>

35:41.882 --> 35:48.145
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:51.725 --> 35:54.709
<i> [soft music]</i>

35:54.728 --> 35:57.379
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:57.397 --> 35:59.047
- Morning.

35:59.065 --> 36:01.158
I came with pastries.

36:04.830 --> 36:06.646
- What happened to you?

36:06.723 --> 36:08.147
- Oh this?
Nothing.

36:08.167 --> 36:11.226
- Uh-huh, and you being here,
that's nothing, too, right?

36:11.244 --> 36:12.744
- Well, after
the Day of the Dead,

36:12.896 --> 36:15.488
I wanted to spend time
with the living.

36:15.490 --> 36:18.157
For my ofrenda,
you have tres leches cake.

36:18.177 --> 36:20.568
I got you some orejas
and a few buñuelos.

36:20.662 --> 36:22.921
- You brought me
day-old dead people bread?

36:23.073 --> 36:26.090
- Mm-hmm, yeah.
- I'll take it.

36:26.167 --> 36:28.685
- So did your friend come?

36:28.762 --> 36:30.002
- Yeah.

36:30.080 --> 36:32.189
- And did you say
what you needed to say?

36:32.265 --> 36:35.275
- Not exactly, but she said
what I needed to hear.

36:37.863 --> 36:40.104
- How did she die?

36:40.181 --> 36:42.014
- [clears throat]

36:42.034 --> 36:43.942
It was Christmas Eve.

36:44.018 --> 36:45.944
We were in a city called
Lashkar Gah.

36:46.020 --> 36:47.478
It's a Taliban stronghold.

36:47.630 --> 36:50.690
And I'd been struggling
with a bad case of CMI.

36:50.767 --> 36:52.116
- What is CMI?

36:52.193 --> 36:53.952
- Chronic multi-symptom
illness,

36:54.028 --> 36:56.213
a grab bag of all of these fun,

36:56.289 --> 36:58.215
medically unexplained
chronic symptoms.

36:58.291 --> 37:00.533
And I was scheduled
to the fly that morning,

37:00.610 --> 37:03.035
but I had the worst headache
of my life.

37:03.113 --> 37:05.055
I could barely stand up,

37:05.131 --> 37:09.375
so Dani offered
to take my place.

37:09.394 --> 37:13.212
And on the way to the airfield,
the vehicle that she was in

37:13.232 --> 37:17.883
that I was supposed to be in
ran over an IED.

37:17.961 --> 37:19.127
- I'm so sorry.

37:19.129 --> 37:21.463
- So I came home
and she didn't,

37:21.481 --> 37:23.481
all because she wanted
to let me sleep off a headache.

37:23.558 --> 37:25.891
- You would have done
the same exact thing for her.

37:25.911 --> 37:27.911
- Now we'll never know.
- I do know.

37:27.988 --> 37:31.414
And I can assure you
she does too.

37:31.566 --> 37:33.733
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:33.810 --> 37:35.293
- [chuckles]

37:38.999 --> 37:42.408
I want to take you out
on a date,

37:42.486 --> 37:46.838
kiss you goodnight,
or good morning, or both.

37:46.914 --> 37:53.603
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:53.755 --> 37:57.165
I gotta get the plane ready.

37:57.167 --> 37:59.851
- Oh, um...

38:00.003 --> 38:04.172
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:04.190 --> 38:05.356
Okay.

38:05.509 --> 38:06.691
<i> - ♪ I need a mouth</i>
<i> to sing this song ♪</i>

38:06.843 --> 38:10.603
<i> ♪ And I need my fingers</i>
<i> to strum along ♪</i>

38:10.605 --> 38:12.104
- Have a safe flight.

38:12.124 --> 38:14.699
<i> - ♪ Sleep until noon</i>
<i> and warm me in winter ♪</i>

38:14.776 --> 38:18.444
- How are you?
- [sighs]

38:18.522 --> 38:20.630
You know what?

38:20.707 --> 38:22.615
I'll be fine.

38:22.634 --> 38:28.120
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:28.198 --> 38:30.882
- I didn't finish
painting the gazebo.

38:31.034 --> 38:32.642
- Somehow, the gazebo
will be all right.

38:32.794 --> 38:34.126
[laughter]

38:34.146 --> 38:35.703
By the way,
I sent some photos of your work

38:35.722 --> 38:37.147
to an art gallery in New York,

38:37.298 --> 38:39.316
and they'd like
to do a studio visit

38:39.467 --> 38:41.634
and select some
of your pieces to show.

38:41.711 --> 38:43.378
- Really?

38:43.396 --> 38:45.638
- I think it's time for you
to do as Jasper said:

38:45.657 --> 38:48.216
believe in yourself.

38:48.234 --> 38:51.328
- Thank you.
- Of course.

38:51.479 --> 38:58.359
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:59.729 --> 39:02.730
- I'm guessing you don't feel
like being alone either.

39:02.749 --> 39:05.842
Want dinner?
- Crab mofongo?

39:05.993 --> 39:08.661
- I can make that happen.

39:08.680 --> 39:10.405
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:10.423 --> 39:15.593
<i> - ♪ Oh, carry me on,</i>
<i> oh, carry me through ♪</i>

39:15.745 --> 39:17.687
- Okay.

39:17.764 --> 39:19.004
This looks beautiful.

39:19.082 --> 39:21.841
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

39:21.918 --> 39:24.009
- Oh, is that your great uncle?

39:24.029 --> 39:26.921
- It is.
Wasn't he dashing?

39:26.940 --> 39:29.532
- Wow, very handsome.

39:31.036 --> 39:33.853
Oh, Elena, you got a note here.

39:33.930 --> 39:35.947
- From who?

39:36.023 --> 39:38.023
- Well, I don't know.
Let's see.

39:38.101 --> 39:40.602
It says it's from Tio.

39:41.195 --> 39:43.046
Oh, wait a minute.
Is that him?

39:43.197 --> 39:45.048
Let me just read it for you.
- No, no, it's okay.

39:45.199 --> 39:48.610
- "My dearest Elena,
my apologies for missing you.

39:48.612 --> 39:51.036
"I had a lovely talk
with Segundo.

39:51.056 --> 39:53.372
"Sounds as if you're doing
a wonderful job.

39:53.450 --> 39:54.949
"You should be proud,

39:54.951 --> 39:59.044
and I'm so pleased to hear you
finally accepted a right hand."

39:59.064 --> 40:02.790
Oh, that's me.
He's talking about me--okay.

40:02.809 --> 40:04.809
"No one should do this job
alone.

40:04.886 --> 40:06.236
"One word of caution:

40:06.387 --> 40:08.312
"I know you love
your cousin Fernando,

40:08.389 --> 40:09.572
"but leave him be, child.

40:09.724 --> 40:11.056
"He's not ready.

40:11.134 --> 40:12.800
"Hope to see you next year.

40:12.819 --> 40:16.329
With love and respect, Tio."

40:18.232 --> 40:20.158
- I can't believe I missed him.

40:20.234 --> 40:22.902
- Elena, who's this cousin
he's talking about?

40:22.979 --> 40:24.921
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:24.998 --> 40:28.149
- I told you that I tried
to say no to this position,

40:28.151 --> 40:33.913
but I didn't tell you
that I did say no.

40:33.932 --> 40:37.325
I was so in love with James.
I was engaged.

40:37.327 --> 40:40.252
I...

40:40.330 --> 40:45.191
so my cousin Fernando,
he stepped in.

40:46.670 --> 40:48.319
And the island wasn't happy.

40:49.764 --> 40:51.322
It didn't end well.

40:52.525 --> 40:55.160
Fernando, he blames me.

40:55.937 --> 40:57.770
I blame me too.

40:57.789 --> 41:00.123
- Elena.

41:00.200 --> 41:02.183
- It's okay.
You know what?

41:02.185 --> 41:04.043
That's a conversation
for another day.

41:05.355 --> 41:08.614
I will tell you
about my uncle's right hand.

41:08.633 --> 41:11.025
He went by Tattoo.

41:11.044 --> 41:13.211
- He had the same tattoo as me?
- Yes, he did.

41:13.287 --> 41:15.788
- Oh.
- And they were inseparable.

41:15.807 --> 41:17.882
- Just like us.
- I suppose so.

41:18.034 --> 41:19.976
- [laughs]

41:20.127 --> 41:21.811
You want to talk about Mel?

41:21.846 --> 41:25.899
- Yes, but not tonight.

41:27.301 --> 41:30.895
Why don't you tell me
a little more about Tattoo?

41:31.881 --> 41:35.066
- He took the arrival
of the plane very seriously.

41:35.218 --> 41:39.162
- Oh.
- He'd ring this gigantic bell.

41:39.239 --> 41:40.663
- Really?
- Yes.

41:40.890 --> 41:41.664
<i> [both laughing]</i>
<i> - That's cute.</i>

41:41.816 --> 41:43.315
<i> - Everybody loved him.</i>

41:43.393 --> 41:46.419
<i> He would always say,</i>
<i> "The plane, the plane!"</i>

41:49.916 --> 41:49.989
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

41:52.919 --> 42:00.141
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
